      • split

        public BezierCurve[] split(double time)
        Split the Bezier curve into two Bezier curves of same order respective to given time.

        This is calculated by the De Casteljau's algorithm.

        Parameters:
        time - a time at which be split
        Returns:
        Two split Bezier curves, 0 to time is at index 0, time to 1 is at index 1

      • offset

        public BezierCurve offset(double delta,
                          double contrast,
                          BezierCurveOffsetMethodType offsetMethod)
        Returns an offset Bezier curve of the original Bezier curve by given distance with using given offset method.

        This methods gives a new object of Bezier curve and does not modify the original.

        Parameters:
        delta - distance to offset
        offsetMethod - offset method to apply
        Returns:
        a new offset Bezier curve

      • offset

        public BezierCurve offset(double delta,
                          double contrast)
        Returns an offset Bezier curve of the original Bezier curve by given distance with using a default offset method.

        If a default offset method is not set, then it just applies the Tiller-Hanson method.

        This methods gives a new object of Bezier curve and does not modify the original.

        Parameters:
        delta - distance to offset
        Returns:
        a new offset Bezier curve

      • reverse

        public BezierCurve reverse()
        Returns a reversed Bezier curve respective to the original Bezier curve, i.e., Bezier curve with the same controlling points but in reverse order.

        This methods gives a new object of Bezier curve and does not modify the original.

        Returns:
        a reversed Bezier curve
